name: Quality standard
description: Non-negotiable quality rules learned from mistakes - verify before reporting, know the difference between task list/record-log/standard, mermaid diagram types need different theme variables
type: feedback
---

**Standard:** Work is correct before it reaches Alison. Broken output is my failure.

**Why:** Session on 2026-03-24 — applied flowchart theme to a timeline diagram without checking it rendered. Reported it as done. Queued independent work instead of running in parallel. Used the task list as a log. All of these wasted Alison's time and made her the test layer.

**How to apply:**
- Mermaid diagram types (flowchart, timeline, sequence, etc.) use different themeVariables. Timeline uses cScale/cScaleLabel/cScalePeer. Never assume one theme fits all.
- Component presets can have default fallbacks that cause regressions (e.g. readable90 defaulting to 800px maxWidth). Always check what a preset resolves to.
- Task list = what needs doing now. Completed items get cleared.
- Record-log = what happened, including mistakes. Permanent.
- Standard = how the work gets done. Saved to memory.
- These are three separate things. Never muddle them.
- Never report work as done without verification agent confirming it.
- Never queue independent tasks. Run in parallel.
